==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===
'''declamation'''
# The act or art of [[declaim]]ing; rhetorical delivery; haranguing; loud speaking in public; especially, the public recitation of speeches as an exercise in schools and colleges; as, the practice declamation by students.
# A set or [[harangue]]; declamatory discourse.
# Pretentious rhetorical display, with more sound than sense; as, mere declamation.

